    <header>
      <h1>Sources</h1>
      <h2>Resources For This Site</h2>
    </header>
    <p>The depth of information I was able to compile would not have been possible without <a href="http://www.archive.org/">Internet Archive</a> and other online resources. What follows is a full list of publications used on this site.</p>
    <ul class="list_sources">
    <li>Batchelor, Albert Stillman. <em>Miscellaneous Revolutionary Documents of New Hampshire.</em> Manchester, New Hampshire: John B. Clarke Co. 1910. Google Books. Web. 2015. Lemuel Crane listed among those signers of the Association Test: page 3. </li>
    <li>Bouton, Nathaniel. <em>Documents And Records Relating To The State of New Hampshire, Volume VIII.</em> Concord, New Hampshire: Edward A. Jenks, State Printer. 1874. Google Books. Web. 2015. Lemuel Crane, page 208.</li>
      <li>Crane, Ellery Bicknell. <em>Genealogy Of The Crane Family. Volume I.</em> Worcester, Mass.: Press Of Charles Hamilton, 1895. Internet Archive. Web. 2014.</li>
      <li>Crane, Ellery Bicknell. <em>Genealogy Of The Crane Family. Volume II.</em> Worcester, Mass.: Press Of Charles Hamilton, 1900. Internet Archive. Web. 2014.</li>
      <li>The Department of Veterans Affairs. <em>National Archives Microfilm Publications Pamphlet Describing M804.</em> Washington D.C.: National Archives Microfilm Publications, 1974. Pamphlet. Page 40. (Zebulon Crane included on roll 684 of M804).</li>
      <li>The Department of Veterans Affairs. <em>Revolutionary War Pension and Bounty—Land—Warrant Application Files. (Rolls 601-800)</em>. Washington D.C.: National Archives Microfilm Publications, 1974. Microfilm, 35mm. Record Group Number: 15, Publication Number: M804D, Roll: 684. (Zebulon and Rhoda Crane, 54 pages in total).</li>
      <li>Fox-Davies, Arthur Charles. <em>A Complete Guide to Heraldry.</em> London: T. C. & E. C. JACK, 1909. Internet Archive. Web. 2014. Heraldry: Page 247.</li>
      <li>Grimm, Donald H. <em>Community History, Zearing, Iowa.</em> Ames, Iowa: Greenwood Printing Company, 1956. Pages 127-128</li>
      <li>Hammond, A. M., Isaac W. <em>The State Of New Hampshire. Rolls Of The Soldiers In The Revolutionary War, 1775, To May, 1777.</em> Concord, New Hampshire: Parsons B. Cogswell., State Printer, 1885. Internet Archive. Web. 2014. Page 265. Zebulon Crane.</li>
      <li>Hervey, William. <em>The Cranes of Suffolk, extr. from &lsquo;The visitation of Suffolke&rsquo;</em>. Lowestoft: S. Tymms, 60, High Street, 1865. Internet Archive. Web. 2014. Pages 3-5.</li>
      <li>Hinman, Royal Ralph. <em>A Catalogue Of The Names Of The Early Puritan Settlers Of The Colony Of Connecticut.</em> Hartford, Connecticut: Press Of Case, Tiffany And Company, 1852. Internet Archive. Web. 2014. </li>
      <li>Jeffords, P.J. <em>The Vermonter, Volumes 21-23.</em> White River Junction, Vermont: Chas. R. Cummings, Year. Internet Archive. Web. 2014. Page: 40. Zebulon Crane.</li>
      <li>Kingsbury, Frank Burnside. <em>History Of The Town Of Surry Cheshire County, New Hampshire.</em> The Concord Press, Concord New Hampshire: Town of Surry, New Hampshire, 1925. Internet Archive. Web. 2014.</li>
      <li>Lee, Francis Bazley. <em>Genealogical and Memorial History of the State of New Jersey. Volume I.</em> New York: Lewis Historical Publishing Company, 1910. Internet Archive. Web. 2014. History of the early family: Pages 15-19, John Crane, Benjamin Crane: Page 18-19. <strong>Needs research. </strong></li>
      <li>Nash, Elizabeth Todd. <em>Fifty Puritan Ancestors, 1628-1660: Genealogical Notes, 1560-1900.</em> New Haven: Tuttle, Morehouse & Taylor Company, 1902. Internet Archive. Web. 2014. John Crane, Benjamin Crane: Page 93, Jonathan Crane: Page 93-94.</li>
      <li>New-England Historic, Genealogical Society. <em>The New England Historical and Genealogical Register, Volume 27.</em> Boston, Mass.: David Clapp & Son, 1873. Internet Archive. Web. 2014. Background and Five Families: Page 76, Benjamin Crane: Page 77, Jonathan Crane: 77, John Crane: 77-78, </li>
      <li>Peck, Thomas Bellows. <em>William Slade of Windsor, Conn. And His Descendants.</em> Keene, New Hampshire: Sentinel Printing Company, 1910. Google Books. Web. 2015. Lemuel and Zebulon: p. 41, 45, 79, 159, 160, (possible burial location of Lemuel’s wife), 181, 194. Reference to origins in England: (page 70-71).</li>
      <li>Stiles, Henry R. <em>Families of Ancient Wethersfield, Connecticut.</em> Westminster, Maryland: Heritage Books, Inc., 2006. Internet Archive. Web. 2014. Benjamin Crane: Page 254, Jonathan Crane: Page: 254-255</li>
      <li>U.S. Census Bureau; United States. Dept. of State. <em>A Census Of Pensioners For Revolutionary Or Military Services.</em> Washington: Blair And Rives, 1841. Internet Archive. Web. 2014. </li>
      <li>U.S. Census Bureau. <a href="/ancestry/docs/census/1870-US-Census-Belle-Plaine-Shawano-County-Wisconsin.pdf">1870 U.S. Census.</a> Belle Plaine, Shawano County, Wisconsin. 1870. Ancestry.com. Web. 2014. Page 14. Ebenezer Crain Jr.</li>
      <li>U.S. Census Bureau. <a href="/ancestry/docs/census/1900-US-Census-Lincoln-Township-Story-County-Iowa.pdf">1900 U.S. Census.</a> Lincoln Township, Story County, Iowa. 1900. Ancestry.com. Web. 2014. Sheet 10. Ebenezer Crain Jr.</li>
      <li>United States War Department. <em>The Pension Roll of 1835: The Indexed Edition, Set. Volume I.</em> Washington: Duff Green, 1835. Google Books. Web. 2014. Page 887. Zebulon Crane: Died September 9, 1828. </li>
      <li>Vermont Historical Society. <em>Proceedings of the Vermont Historical Society 1903-1904.</em> Burlington: Free Press Association, 1905. Internet Archive. Web. 2014. Zebulon Crane: Page 119.</li>
      <!---<li>AuthorLastName, AuthorFirstName. Title of Book. Publication Location: Publisher, Year. Online Library or Retrieval Service. Web. Day month year of access. </li>--->
    </ul>
